</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0B3869FC9AFCFDFEBBFA34" lastPageId="604" lastPageNumber="605" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFC9AFCFDFAF1FAEB" blockId="602.[810,1452,581,2070]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFC9AFCFDFBA4FC8C" bold="true" box="[863,1121,819,845]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFB7AFCFDFAF3FC8F" box="[1215,1334,819,846]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406A</figureCitation>
) elongate, cylindrical, straight or curved, consisting of prosome and unsegmented free abdomen. Body length variable, 9.25 mmin relatively small, figured specimen; body width 0.93 mm. Prosome unsegmented: cephalosome notarticulated from remaining part of prosome, but discernible by lateral expansions(
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFC77FC31FBE6FBDB" box="[946,1059,1023,1050]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig.406B</figureCitation>
);antennalandrostralregionnarrow. All legs inserted in pedigerous region confined to anterior part of prosome. Genital openings present in posterior region of prosome. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFB4EFBABFB3AFB41" box="[1163,1279,1125,1152]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406C</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, as long as wide, positioned posteroventrally on prosome. Caudal rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFC17FB67FB88FB05" box="[978,1101,1193,1220]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406D</figureCitation>
) 2.6 timeslongerthan wide (140×54 μm), narrowing in middle and ornamented with numerous papillae scattered over surface: armed with 6 setae (2 outer lateral, 2 subdistal, and 2 distal).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFC9AFAFCFA46F9F8" blockId="602.[810,1452,581,2070]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFC13FAFFFB8BFA8D" box="[982,1102,1329,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406E</figureCitation>
) evenly tapering, aslongas wide. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFC3AFA9DFBB3FAAF" box="[1023,1142,1363,1390]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406F</figureCitation>
) unsegmented but clearly divisible into 2 parts; proximal part extremely swollen, globular, armed with 3 small setae distally; distal part narrow, digitiform, armed with 11 setae and 1 aesthetasc. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFC5CFA15FBCBFA37" box="[921,1038,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406G</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented; coxa and basis broad and unarmed; unsegmentedendopod bearing 2 inner and 3 or 4 outer, minute setae, plus straight terminal claw.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFC9AF98FFB79F871" blockId="602.[810,1452,581,2070]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
Labrum hardly observable. Mouthparts consisting of mandible, maxillule, and maxilla, all represented by unsegmented lobes bearing plumose setae. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFABBF94BFCACF903" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406H</figureCitation>
) with 3 long medial and 2 to 4 (3 is common) shorter apical setae. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFBF1F907FB58F925" box="[1076,1181,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406I</figureCitation>
) with 3 long and 3 short setae (2 medial, 3 apical, and 1 outer). Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFAFFF925FA61F8C7" box="[1338,1444,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Fig. 406J</figureCitation>
) consisting of broader proximal half and narrower distal half (interpretable as 2-segmented condition depending on viewing angle), armed with 1 seta proximally and 3 setaeon apex; ornamented 2 patches of setules and more than 10 papillae. Maxilliped absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B3869FC9AF876FD1AFB02" blockId="602.[810,1452,581,2070]" lastBlockId="604.[136,778,1057,1220]" lastPageId="604" lastPageNumber="605" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFC1FF876FBB8F813" box="[986,1149,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 406" captionStartId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@603.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="603" captionText="FIGURE 406. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, posterior end of prosome and urosome, ventral; D, left caudal ramus, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla; K, leg 1; L, leg 2. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, K, L, 0.05 mm; F–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Figs. 406K, L</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED0B386FFB49F876FB28F813" box="[1164,1261,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 407" captionStartId="604.[136,245,955,981]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,234,881]" captionTargetId="figure-21@604.[136,1451,216,901]" captionTargetPageId="604" captionText="FIGURE 407. Scolecodes pugetensis sp. nov., female. A, leg 3; B, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592132" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592132/files/figure.png" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">407A, B</figureCitation>
) biramous, each with incompletely 2-segmented protopod, 2-segmented exopod, and unsegmented endopod. Protopods of legs 1– 4 each with outer seta derived from basis; other armature elements absent. All setae on rami short and broad, with nipple-like tip. Number of setae variable between individuals and between left and right legs in single individual. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED0A386EFF4DF8BDFAB3F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592130" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592130/files/figure.png" pageId="603" pageNumber="604" startId="603.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[242,1341,217,1836]" targetPageId="603">
