<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0D3869FF78FA30FBD5FBBE" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0D3869FF78FA30FBD5FBBE" blockId="604.[136,778,1499,2070]" lastBlockId="604.[810,1452,1057,1151]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FF78FA30FEEFF9D9" bold="true" box="[189,298,1534,1560]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0D3869FEFCFA33FDF1F9D6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[313,564,1533,1559]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FEFCFA33FDF1F9D6" box="[313,564,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Scolecodes pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0D3869FDF8FA30FD5CF9D9" box="[573,665,1534,1560]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FDF8FA30FD57F9D9" bold="true" box="[573,658,1534,1560]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED0D3869FF12F9EEFEC2F9FB" box="[215,263,1568,1594]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0D3869FEB0F9EEFDCEF9F8" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="1931" box="[373,523,1567,1594]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huntsmani">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FEB0F9EEFE46F9FB" box="[373,387,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FE53F9D1FDCEF9F8" box="[406,523,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">huntsmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and both species can inhabit solitary ascidians of the same genus (
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0D3869FDBDF98CFD79F99A" authorityName="Molina" authorityYear="1782" box="[632,700,1602,1627]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Pyuridae" genus="Pyura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FDBDF98CFD79F99A" box="[632,700,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Pyura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the same zoogeographic region. The number of setae on the swimminglegsobservedby 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0D3869FE05F948FDEAF961" author="Illg" box="[448,559,1669,1696]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0D3869FDFCF948FD45F960" author="Illg, P. L." box="[569,640,1670,1697]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" pagination="69 - 74" part="18" refId="ref329022" refString="Illg, P. L. (1970 b) Occurrence in Sagami Bay, Japan, of Scolecodes, a remarkable copepod parasite of ascidians. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 18, 69 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175627" title="Occurrence in Sagami Bay, Japan, of Scolecodes, a remarkable copepod parasite of ascidians" type="journal article" year="1970">1970b</bibRefCitation>
) fallswithin the range of variability exhibited in our material. The mandible, maxillule, and maxilla of female 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0D3869FDBDF904FCCFF925" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="1931" box="[632,778,1738,1764]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huntsmani">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FDBDF904FD43F925" box="[632,646,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FD50F904FCCFF925" box="[661,778,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">huntsmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0D3869FE84F922FE31F8C6" author="Dudley, P. L." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[321,500,1772,1799]" journalOrPublisher="University of Washington Press, Seattle and London" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" refId="ref327924" refString="Dudley, P. L. (1966) Development and Systematics of Some Pacific Marine Symbiotic Copepods. A Study of the Biology of the Notodelphyidae, associates of Ascidians. University of Washington Press, Seattle and London, 282 pp." title="Development and Systematics of Some Pacific Marine Symbiotic Copepods. A Study of the Biology of the Notodelphyidae, associates of Ascidians" type="book" year="1966">
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FED0D3869FE84F922FE56F8C7" box="[321,403,1772,1798]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">Dudley</collectingRegion>
(1966)
</bibRefCitation>
are not significantly different from these limbs in our specimens. Despite these similarities and the variability observed, these two species are not conspecific because the exopods of legs 1–4 are 2-segmented in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0D3869FE5AF8BAFDF6F84C" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[415,563,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FE5AF8BAFE68F84F" box="[415,429,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FE78F8BAFDF6F84C" box="[445,563,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">pugetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0D3869FDF8F8BAFD5CF84F" box="[573,665,1908,1934]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FDF8F8BAFD51F84F" bold="true" box="[573,660,1908,1934]" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but only 1-segmented in adults of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0D3869FE71F858FD8FF871" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="1931" box="[436,586,1942,1968]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huntsmani">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FE71F858FE07F871" box="[436,450,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0D3869FE10F858FD8FF871" box="[469,586,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="604" pageNumber="605">huntsmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0D3869FF4DF876FEC5F812" author="Illg" box="[136,256,1976,2003]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="604" pageNumber="605" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958)</bibRefCitation>
and illustrated by 
